E. coli O157 - Japan (Tokyo) 20010416.0754
[1
Date: 17 Apr 2001
From: Narufumi Suganuma <suganuma@fmsrsa.fukui-med.ac.jp>
Source: Japanese Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare website [edited
(in Japanese)

[Regarding the recent _E. coli_ O157 outbreak, the Japanese Ministry of
Health, Labour and Welfare announced that 264 patients [had been positively
identified, among whom 76 were asymptomatic. 178 of patients [had eaten
contaminated meat. Bacteria isolated from 130 patients showed identical
PFGE pattern.
Below is a detailed list of numbers of patients as of 17:00, 13 Apr 2001:
Prefecture / No. of patients (asymptomatic) / had contaminated meat
(asymptomatic) / identical DNA pattern
Chiba / 177(51) / 134(38) / 90
Saitama / 29(10) / 15(2) / 12
Tokyo / 15(5) / 7(2) / 4
Kanagawa / 17(5) / 14(4) / 10
Gunma / 8(4) / 1 / 7
Ibaragi / 4 / 2 / 2
Yamagata / 3 / 1 / 1
Total / 264(76) / 178(46) / 130
_
Narufumi Suganuma
